The paper deals with decision problems for Petri nets with names, which are a type of formal language used in computer science. The paper discusses topics such as decidability and undecidability, Well Structured Transition Systems, and Ackermann-hardness. These topics are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
